# Architecture — Lib vs Services

## `packages/anomx/` (core library)

- **Zero imports** of FastAPI, Streamlit, Dagster, ARQ, uvicorn
- Must work via `pip install anomx`, CLI, or notebook — standalone
- Business logic lives here: connectors, detectors, benchmark, explain, storage repos
- **mypy strict** on all `anomx/` code

## `services/*` (application layers)

- Thin wrappers that call `anomx` — never duplicate core logic
- `services/api/` — FastAPI routes, workers (Phase 5+), schemas
- `services/dashboard/` — Streamlit (Phase 5, not yet scaffolded)
- `services/orchestrator/` — Dagster assets wrapping `anomx` functions (Phase 7)

## Dependency direction

```
services/*  →  packages/anomx
packages/anomx  ↛  services/*
```

## Interfaces (Protocol-based)

`Source`, `Sink`, `Detector`, `Alerter` in `anomx/core/interfaces.py` — extend via new modules, not by editing services.

## Postgres schema

Tables: `streams`, `runs`, `observations`, `scores`, `alerts` — defined in `infra/postgres/init.sql`. Extend via migrations, not ad-hoc DDL in app code.
